    <p>GLP-1 medications prescribed for medical weight loss (not cosmetic purposes) are typically eligible for Health Savings Account (HSA) or Flexible Spending Account (FSA) reimbursement. This allows you to pay with pre-tax dollars, effectively saving 20-35% depending on your tax bracket.</p>
    
    <h3>4. Look for First-Time Discounts</h3>
    <p>Many providers offer promotional pricing for new customers, ranging from $50-150 off your first month. Always check for promo codes or affiliate discounts before signing up.</p>
    
    <h3>5. Commit to Multi-Month Plans</h3>
    <p>Some providers offer reduced pricing if you commit to 3-6 month subscriptions. While this requires upfront payment, the monthly cost can be 15-30% lower than month-to-month pricing.</p>
    
    <h2>Cheapest Option by Medication Type</h2>
    
    <h3>Cheapest Semaglutide (Wegovy Alternative)</h3>
    <p>The most affordable semaglutide options are:</p>
    <ul>
      {sortedByPrice.filter(p => p.medications.some(m => m.toLowerCase().includes('semaglutide'))).slice(0, 3).map(p => (
        <li><strong>{p.name}:</strong> {p.monthlyPrice} - <a href={`/reviews/${p.slug}/`}>Review</a></li>
      ))}
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Cheapest Tirzepatide (Mounjaro/Zepbound Alternative)</h3>
    <p>The most affordable tirzepatide options are:</p>
    <ul>
      {sortedByPrice.filter(p => p.medications.some(m => m.toLowerCase().includes('tirzepatide'))).slice(0, 3).map(p => (
        <li><strong>{p.name}:</strong> {p.monthlyPrice} - <a href={`/reviews/${p.slug}/`}>Review</a></li>
      ))}
    </ul>
    
