    <ol>
      <li><strong>Licensed pharmacy source:</strong> Verify the provider uses 503A or 503B licensed compounding pharmacies</li>
      <li><strong>Medical oversight:</strong> Ensure a licensed healthcare provider reviews your medical history and prescribes the medication</li>
      <li><strong>Proper ingredients:</strong> Confirm the compounded medication uses pharmaceutical-grade semaglutide or tirzepatide</li>
      <li><strong>Quality testing:</strong> Ask if the pharmacy tests for purity and potency (reputable providers will)</li>
    </ol>
    
    <p>All providers on CompareWeightMeds meet these safety standards. We do not list providers using questionable sourcing or lacking medical oversight.</p>
    
    <h2>Cost Breakdown: What's Included?</h2>
    <p>When comparing prices, make sure you're looking at the total cost. Most providers include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>‚úÖ Medication (semaglutide or tirzepatide)</li>
      <li>‚úÖ Medical consultation with licensed provider</li>
      <li>‚úÖ Prescription review and approval</li>
      <li>‚úÖ Shipping (cold-chain packaging)</li>
      <li>‚úÖ Syringes, needles, alcohol wipes (for injectables)</li>
    </ul>
    
    <p>Watch out for hidden costs like:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>‚ùå Separate consultation fees</li>
      <li>‚ùå Monthly membership fees</li>
      <li>‚ùå Lab work charges</li>
      <li>‚ùå Price increases at higher dosages</li>
    </ul>
    
    <FAQSection faqs={faqs} />
    
    <h2>Bottom Line: How to Get the Cheapest GLP-1</h2>
    <p>For most patients without insurance coverage, the cheapest way to access GLP-1 medications is through compounded versions from telehealth providers starting at $179-249 per month. Providers like ${cheapest[0].name} (${cheapest[0].monthlyPrice}) offer the lowest entry price with transparent all-in pricing.</p>
    
    <p>If you have insurance that covers Wegovy or Zepbound, brand-name medications may actually be cheaper (as low as $25-50 copay). Check with providers like ${providers.filter(p => p.insurance).slice(0, 2).map(p => p.name).join(' or ')} to explore insurance options.</p>
    
    <div style="text-align: center; margin-top: 48px;">
      <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary" style="font-size: 1.1rem; padding: 16px 32px;">
        Compare All ${providers.length} Providers ‚Üí
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
